#   BLAME-006b: `commit:?<root>` token-diffs the whole initial tree (O(repo), seconds)

Loading the parentless ROOT commit (`commit:?c7184818`) takes ~4.4s because it
token-level weave-diffs the ENTIRE initial-import tree as all-INS, where a
one-sided (vs-empty) diff should be a cheap raw all-add. Split from [BLAME-006]
(the perf half). Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Timing: root commit *4.35s / 3853 lines*; a typical commit *0.16s / 183*.
 -  Path: `be commit:?<sha>` (`beagle/BE.cli.c:332` + relay `:453-459`) runs graf
    `diff:?<sha>`; `graf_first_parent_hex` returns GRAFNONE for the parentless root
    (`GRAF.exe.c:75`), so it falls to `GRAF.exe.c:505` → `GRAFDiffTreeRefs`
    (`graf/DIFFREF.c:564`) which TOKEN-diffs every one of the 291 initial-import
    files as all-INS (`@@ -1,0 +1,N @@`) — O(repo), tokenizing+weave-diffing all.
 -  Semantically a root "commit show" IS the whole tree (diff vs empty); the win is
    to make whole-tree all-INS CHEAP, not to change what's shown.

### Goals
 -  `commit:?<root>` (and any one-sided / vs-empty diff) loads in time proportional
    to the commit, not the repo — emit raw all-add without token-level weave diff
    when one side is empty.

### Constraints
 -  Output unchanged (same all-add lines, same hunks); only the cost drops. graf
    change gates for review. Add a timing/shape test.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  At the diff entry (`DIFFREF.c:564` / the WEAVE diff core), detect a one-empty-side
    diff and short-circuit to a raw all-INS emit (skip tokenize+LCS) for each file.

### TODOs
-[ ] Repro: time `be commit:?<root>` vs a normal commit; confirm O(repo) hot path
      in `GRAFDiffTreeRefs`.
-[ ] Fix: empty-side short-circuit (raw all-add) in the tree-diff/weave path.
-[ ] Test: root/whole-tree commit-show is bounded; output byte-identical to before.

### Blockers and bummers
 -  Pairs with [BLAME-006a] (the correctness half) — independent; land separately.

##  Outcome
 -  *LANDED `8d66369c`* (FF child of `3dc19b0a`; msg `BLAME-006b: skip token-diff of
    binary blobs`). Scan's "291-file all-INS" premise was wrong — the 4.35s was one
    9.5 MB binary (`dog/dogs.png`) tokenized in 3.17s. Fix (graf): `WEAVEFromBlobRm`
    (one-sided/vs-empty short-circuit to raw all-add) + `diffref_is_binary` (git's
    NUL-in-first-8000 heuristic) so binaries are never token-diffed; root commit-show
    4.35s→1.52s, text output byte-identical. Test: Case I in `beagle/test/be-diff-projector.sh`.
    302/302. NB landing: reconciled a `graf/DIFFREF.c` overlap with DIFF-002 (both survive,
    verified on trunk); the POSTCFLCT marker false-positive on `graf/WEAVE.c` required the
    documented `--force` conflict-scan bypass (see [POST-006]/[POST-017]).

